It&#8217;s understood he was caught in rip currents while swimming with his sister. CAPE TOWN The body of a 17-year old boy has been recovered after an extensive three-day search.The teen disappeared while swimming at a Wilderness beach on Saturday.It s understood he was caught in rip currents while swimming with his sister.National Sea Rescue Institute spokesperson Craig Lambinon says: A police dive unit recovered the body of the 17-year-old in Wilderness Beach yesterday. NSRI were called on scene and on arrival on-scene forensic pathologist found that police were already attending to the scene. Police have opened an inquest docket. Meanwhile, officials are still searching for the bodies of an 18-year-old from Gugulethu who disappeared while swimming with friends at the Mnandi beach and that of a man who went missing at the Monwabisi beach on Monday.(Edited by Leeto M Khoza)